Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.39,0:01:47.85,Warning,Warning,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,530)}Watch the Slip Arc in a bright room and at a safe distance from your TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.51,0:01:45.40,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Don't do it. You'll be mincemeat \Nif you fall from this high up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.40,0:01:46.99,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Don't get the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.99,0:01:51.49,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I just want to know if I \Nstill have the wings to fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.49,0:01:53.38,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,And I came here to find out, is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.11,0:01:58.14,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Life is precious. Don't throw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.85,0:02:01.85,Ep Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(480,1)}Life, Death, and Shades
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.24,0:02:04.36,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Look who's talking!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.36,0:02:06.52,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,You totally wanna lay waste to a life!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.52,0:02:09.31,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,You're totally trying to kill someone, \Nright? You're an assassin, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.31,0:02:11.91,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get the wrong idea. \NI'm just here to hunt boars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.91,0:02:15.11,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,From how far away are you \Ntrying to hunt boars?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.11,0:02:18.06,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Really, don't be stupid. \NDon't commit a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.06,0:02:19.55,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna hear that from a suicidal man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.55,0:02:20.90,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna hear that from an assassin!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.90,0:02:22.41,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna hear that from a \Nman wearing filthy-ass shades.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.41,0:02:24.26,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna hear that from \Na man wearing lame-ass shades!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.26,0:02:25.81,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Your shades are more lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.81,0:02:27.88,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, your shades are more lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.82,0:02:30.13,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Let me be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.13,0:02:33.65,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't care less what kind of shades \Nyou wear, or when and where you wear them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.65,0:02:34.88,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,We're talking about shades now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.24,0:02:38.52,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, do you really \Nhave it in you to jump?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.28,0:02:44.39,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,You've been doing this every \Nday for the past month.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.23,0:02:50.22,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I want to die,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.22,0:02:54.34,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,thinking about shades smashing into \Nthe ground makes my shades tremble.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.76,0:02:58.66,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,You're an assassin, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.66,0:03:02.91,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know a way to die that isn't scary \Nor sad and doesn't hurt or break shades?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.91,0:03:05.18,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,You're basically saying you don't wanna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.72,0:03:08.29,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,If nothing else, I want my shades to live on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.29,0:03:09.92,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you just take them off before you die?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.30,0:03:11.72,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an assassin, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.72,0:03:14.49,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,If I stop to think about how my \Nvictims feel, I couldn't do my—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.49,0:03:15.38,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.38,0:03:18.23,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I could just have you kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.23,0:03:18.71,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.71,0:03:23.67,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,You could send me to heaven in one shot, \Nwithout letting me feel any pain or fear!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.67,0:03:27.14,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Screw you. Do you have any idea how much \Nmoney is involved in each of my shots?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.61,0:03:29.38,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I don't waste my rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.38,0:03:30.96,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Be it when I'm killing my targets
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.96,0:03:32.86,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,or when I'm making love to women.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.67,0:03:36.18,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,All it takes is one shot. \NIt's over in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.18,0:03:38.26,Main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Done already, CEO?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.26,0:03:40.25,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,That's my creed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.93,0:03:45.49,sign_5105_49_One_and_Done,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,One and Done
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.25,0:03:43.05,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,and that's where my moniker of \N"One and Done Synshen" comes from.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.05,0:03:45.49,sign_5132_50_Synshen,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Synshen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.05,0:03:45.49,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,They're just mocking you for \Nshooting your load early!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.10,0:03:48.35,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll have to kill myself \Nright here and now, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.35,0:03:49.12,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.12,0:03:50.74,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.74,0:03:53.94,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,You head to the roof of that skyscraper now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.88,0:03:54.61,sign_5416_56_Welcome_to_Earth,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to Earth!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.94,0:03:56.77,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,My target is taking part in \Na welcoming party there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.77,0:03:58.47,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,You're really hunting a boar?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.47,0:04:02.30,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Once I give the signal, jump off the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:05.24,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,When you fall into my crosshairs \Nthat will be aimed at my target,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:09.85,sign_5642_60_Me,SignB,0000,0000,0000,,Me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:09.85,sign_5642_61_Boar,SignR,0000,0000,0000,,Boar
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.24,0:04:07.72,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I will pierce you both through with one shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.72,0:04:08.63,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,That should do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.63,0:04:10.66,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you making this too hard for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.36,0:04:14.27,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,And the shades are being \Nsmashed to bits anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.79,0:04:17.28,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I guess around here is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.75,0:04:19.53,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Now I just have to wait for the signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.02,0:04:21.94,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,With this, I can finally go to heaven—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.94,0:04:23.03,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.03,0:04:25.95,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be mincemeat if you \Nfall from this high up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.95,0:04:28.67,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,Put yourself in the shoes of the lady \Nwho runs the cutlet place down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.67,0:04:30.54,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, before all that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.24,0:04:34.12,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,Life is precious. Don't throw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.67,0:04:36.92,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! Here, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.92,0:04:39.92,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,There's an assassin here, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.92,0:04:42.71,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't want to die, leave at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.71,0:04:43.93,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,But I do want to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.36,0:04:48.68,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that One and Done Synshen \Nis targeting this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.68,0:04:52.94,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Could he be an assassin hired \Nby Synshen's enemy to kill him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.94,0:04:57.28,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go tell him right now, or the \Nassassin who's gonna kill me will lose his...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.98,0:04:59.34,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.67,0:05:04.95,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Synshen is on that rooftop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:07.70,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,I must thank you for telling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.70,0:05:12.59,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you can just shoot \Nme in the head in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.59,0:05:14.46,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.79,0:05:16.70,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,Even an assassin has his creed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.70,0:05:19.98,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,The only people I kill are\Nscumbags like Synshen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.68,0:05:22.22,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,Be it targets or women,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.22,0:05:24.22,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,I don't go after those on \Nthe straight and narrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.22,0:05:26.35,Main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Done already, CEO?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.35,0:05:29.91,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,That's where my moniker \N"Quickdraw Synron" comes from.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.87,0:05:33.06,Quick,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Quickdraw
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.62,0:05:33.06,Synron,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Synron
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.91,0:05:31.42,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Your moniker has nothing \Nto do with your creed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.42,0:05:33.06,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Are all assassins too \Nquick to shoot their loads?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.38,0:05:34.63,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,How about we do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.63,0:05:37.44,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,You head back to that building
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.44,0:05:41.90,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,and lure Synshen somewhere I can snipe him
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.90,0:05:43.45,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,using a scummy tactic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.94,0:05:48.45,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,If you do that, I promise to shoot \Nboth you scumbags in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:51.45,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,This has gotten even more complicated!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.69,0:05:53.48,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I came here to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.48,0:05:56.18,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I playing accomplice \Nin an assassination?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.78,0:05:59.75,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,S-Synshen...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.75,0:06:01.71,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,They got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.71,0:06:03.21,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.21,0:06:06.36,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy already has the \Nentire city under its control.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.78,0:06:13.32,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to let you know that \Nyour life is in grave danger...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.32,0:06:15.69,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.69,0:06:20.44,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,B-Before I die, could you take me up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.44,0:06:21.51,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.51,0:06:23.44,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Hell yeah! He fell for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.88,0:06:26.99,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get you to a hospital right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.99,0:06:30.28,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,No, forget that. Just take \Nme up there before I die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.28,0:06:33.89,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,You moron! Don't be so quick \Nto say you're gonna die!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.89,0:06:35.29,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he so full of passion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.29,0:06:37.51,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I told you that I'd kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.51,0:06:38.99,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare die until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.99,0:06:40.92,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,He's a much nicer guy than I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.28,0:06:44.16,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait. Aren't you a professional assassin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.16,0:06:46.43,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you should \Nleave your job unfinished?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.43,0:06:49.99,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think is more important? \NA job, or a person's life?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.99,0:06:53.11,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,And who was it that was taking \Npeople's lives on the job?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.11,0:06:54.70,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Damn those scumbags.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.70,0:06:57.44,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, you're the scumbag. \NDon't forget where you stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.44,0:07:00.88,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,First they take my sister, and now \Nthey want to take my friend, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.88,0:07:03.53,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,When did we become friends?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.98,0:07:05.03,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.03,0:07:07.07,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a sniper on that rooftop, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.07,0:07:09.83,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Synron-san! \NThis is as far as I can go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.83,0:07:12.38,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, he's actually a really nice guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.38,0:07:13.54,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be the decoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.54,0:07:16.41,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,In the meantime, you use this \Nto take out that sniper.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.41,0:07:18.55,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Asking a half-dead guy to kill someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.55,0:07:21.36,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell if he's a nice \Nguy or a bad guy anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.36,0:07:22.59,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Don't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.59,0:07:25.17,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, I came here to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.17,0:07:27.17,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.17,0:07:29.43,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I came here to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.43,0:07:32.32,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care anymore! I'll kill or whatever!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.32,0:07:36.64,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,If I actually try to kill \NSynron, I'm sure he'll kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.56,0:07:38.89,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,He's already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.26,0:07:41.27,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.07,0:07:44.77,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry, I screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.16,0:07:50.64,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,I panicked and rushed to kill Synshen, \Nbut I failed to notice my rounds were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.64,0:07:52.34,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,He took that chance to hit you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.34,0:07:53.41,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,No, like I said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.80,0:07:57.22,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.22,0:07:58.91,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,That really is one hell of a screw-up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.91,0:08:02.91,Main,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't have any rounds, I can't kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.91,0:08:04.26,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need those round ones for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.26,0:08:07.26,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I'm no longer fit to be a sniper.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.26,0:08:09.66,Main,G,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Done already, CEO?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.30,0:08:10.93,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You were never fit and firing there anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.32,0:08:13.34,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,But it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:16.93,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I did have the rounds, \NI wouldn't have been able to fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.75,0:08:19.66,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Some scumbag he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.66,0:08:23.08,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe he acted like that in front \Nof his enemy in the middle of a hit job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.48,0:08:27.74,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why my boss is \Nbeing targeted by Synshen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:31.65,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what people call him behind his back:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.65,0:08:33.20,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,"slave trader."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.82,0:08:37.20,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,The stuff he peddles includes people
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.68,0:08:41.12,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,and Synshen's kid sister who was \Nwith him when he was an orphan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.21,0:08:46.21,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Only then did he start walking \Ndown the path of a scumbag.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.64,0:08:49.59,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,So when I saw him do that, \NI realized something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.04,0:08:53.59,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,He came here as a brother \Ntrying to save his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.98,0:08:57.18,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you tell him something for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.97,0:09:00.35,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,"I don't have the rounds \Nto shoot you with anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.23,0:09:06.23,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,but I still have enough \Nto unload into scumbags!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.73,0:09:11.15,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Unload those into me, not scumbags!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.15,0:09:12.66,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done with this crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.66,0:09:15.04,Internal,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just gonna jump off the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.74,0:09:21.20,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,It's been 20 years since we were sold off.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.20,0:09:23.75,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Our appearances have changed \Ncompletely since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.75,0:09:26.25,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,and we even cast our names aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.25,0:09:31.14,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems we both chose to walk down \Nthe same path to get our sibling back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.14,0:09:33.26,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have the rounds \Nto shoot me with anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.82,0:09:37.98,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiko, you never had any \Nround ones to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.64,0:09:42.03,Main,Boar,0000,0000,0000,,You siblings would've been \Nbetter off killing each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.03,0:09:46.23,Main,Boar,0000,0000,0000,,If you two can't settle things \Nyourselves, I can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.15,0:09:50.57,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,You were always like that, Ichiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.57,0:09:54.53,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,You loved to dress up like \Na boy and play with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.87,0:09:58.66,Flashback,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,You're so mean, Ichiro-nii!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.66,0:10:01.20,Flashback,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,I'm out of water here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.54,0:10:03.66,Flashback,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I keep telling you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.97,0:10:06.92,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,You're too quick to shoot your load.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.92,0:10:09.99,Flashback,Gol2,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez! How can I win, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.99,0:10:11.99,Flashback,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.05,0:10:16.50,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,You put everything you have into one shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.05,0:10:21.06,Main,Boar,0000,0000,0000,,Is he going to shoot me \Nalong with his sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.06,0:10:24.31,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready for my best shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.18,0:10:26.56,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Because I've already fired it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:31.83,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,If you can kill me, I'd like to see you try!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.52,0:10:46.39,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,Man, in the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.04,0:10:50.99,Main,Mad,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't die!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.51,0:10:59.91,Main,Gol,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like your wings are still right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.97,0:11:06.87,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,In our job, fieldwork is everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.87,0:11:10.84,sign_15822_200_Special_Crash_Co,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Special Crash Course for \NUpper Management Candidates
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.30,0:11:10.84,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,But in any organization, the skilled \Nemployees are the first to leave the field
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.15,0:11:14.12,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,and take up leadership roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.12,0:11:20.44,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,All of you master investigators will \Nlearn how the nectar of authority tastes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.44,0:11:25.14,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't promote you just so you could rot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.14,0:11:27.85,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,What I'm basically trying to say is,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.85,0:11:30.18,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,no matter how far up the ladder you climb,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.18,0:11:32.93,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,never forget the field where you came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.93,0:11:37.72,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Pearls of wisdom from the super boss who \Nspends taxpayer money on cabaret clubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.72,0:11:39.17,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be like that, Toshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.17,0:11:44.16,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need a crash course. \NWe're drowning in fieldwork every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.61,0:11:51.17,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, we're full of idiots who think \Ndesk work means sleeping on a desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.57,0:11:54.17,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,And who is he calling master investigators?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.49,0:11:58.86,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,These useless rich kids who landed comfy \Njobs using their family names and contacts?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.86,0:12:00.41,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Toshi! They can hear you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.41,0:12:02.30,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,I want them to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.30,0:12:06.81,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry. You're a rich kid from \Na famous family too, aren't you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.92,0:12:10.52,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Mimawarigumi Chief Sasaki-dono?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.83,0:12:15.13,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,No need to worry, Shinsengumi \NVice Chief Hijikata-dono.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.13,0:12:20.95,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Once I become director-general, I'll effect \Nelite reform by the elite for the elite.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.45,0:12:23.93,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,For starters, maybe I should \Nfire that napping thorny
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.93,0:12:27.41,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,and the dummy spreading secondhand smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.81,0:12:29.65,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, Nobume-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.83,0:12:34.84,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Elite reform, my ass! Your subordinate \Nis napping in class, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.84,0:12:36.09,Main,Nob,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not napping.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.09,0:12:37.20,Main,Nob,0000,0000,0000,,I'm snacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.21,0:12:38.92,sign_17964_227_Japanese_for__Go,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Japanese for \NGood Kids
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.20,0:12:38.92,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,They're both equally bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.92,0:12:41.38,Main,Oki,0000,0000,0000,,Hate to break it to ya, \Nbut I'm not napping, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.84,0:12:45.72,Main,Oki,0000,0000,0000,,I was pretending so people wouldn't figure \Nout during recess that I have no friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.72,0:12:47.00,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Why the triumphant look?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.00,0:12:49.02,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you two competing over school tropes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.02,0:12:53.57,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Also, a guy messing with his phone during \Na lecture has no right to complain to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.57,0:12:56.25,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,I'm merely noting down the important points.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.25,0:12:59.77,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm using nicotine to clear \Nmy head so I can pay attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.77,0:13:01.16,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, game over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.16,0:13:03.32,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,So you were just playing a mobile game!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.03,0:13:07.04,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it down, you louts!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.65,0:13:10.16,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Beat it to the hallway \Nin under three seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.57,0:13:12.58,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,or I'll blow your brains out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.58,0:13:13.79,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,One...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.96,0:13:18.30,Ep Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(480,1)}All the Answers \NCan Be Found in the Field
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.49,0:13:16.49,Main,All,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to two and three?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.30,0:13:20.59,sign_15822_200_Special_Crash_Co,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Special Crash Course for \NUpper Management Candidates
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.86,0:13:21.08,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,So, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.08,0:13:26.17,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have these guys act as guinea pigs, \Nexperience a crime scene, and investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.17,0:13:29.35,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a simulation, but I want you \Nall to rack your brains along with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.78,0:13:32.85,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if it's a simulation \Nor whatever. Bring it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.85,0:13:36.31,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, though we'd rather not be compared \Nto these people. Right, Nobume-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.31,0:13:39.32,sign_19405_250_Records_of_the_T,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Records of the Three Kingdoms
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.62,0:13:39.67,Main,Nob,0000,0000,0000,,If you defeat Cao Cao \Nearly, you lose motivation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.67,0:13:41.74,Main,Nob,0000,0000,0000,,and stop caring about uniting China.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.74,0:13:45.16,Main,Oki,0000,0000,0000,,Cao Cao can be the last boss, then. \NWhoever defeats Wei first wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.16,0:13:47.08,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, he said simulation, but not that kind!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.08,0:13:50.60,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,A fictional crime scene \Nwill be displayed in VR.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.60,0:13:54.76,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Analyze the crime using the clues at \Nthe scene and identify the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.93,0:14:01.65,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.65,0:14:03.30,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,It's like the real thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.30,0:14:07.52,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,This is HQ, you know. We have \Nall the cutting-edge tech.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.52,0:14:10.37,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,And we have files on every \Nkind of case imaginable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:15.65,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,This case, based on a massive amount of \Ndata, is no different from the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.22,0:14:20.42,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Here's the gist of it. A corpse \Nwas found on this river bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:23.19,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,An old lady living nearby \Nwas the first to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.89,0:14:29.16,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,She testified that she was here to do laundry \Nwhen she saw it drift by from upstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.26,0:14:35.04,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of case is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.04,0:14:39.21,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,HQ's case files clearly have \Nfolktales from Japan mixed in!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.21,0:14:41.77,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,I hear a similar case happened in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.77,0:14:44.05,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell it did! This is Momotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.49,0:14:47.37,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know for sure \Nthat this is Momotaro yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.37,0:14:49.85,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, he obviously is. \NHe was even inside a peach.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.85,0:14:52.65,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Acting on misconceptions \Ncan lead to mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.65,0:14:54.48,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,The granny was here to do laundry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.48,0:14:58.10,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Pops, was the peach already \Nsplit when it was found?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.10,0:15:02.72,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Granny testified that she pulled it out \Nin this state when it came drifting by.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.72,0:15:05.05,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,We're actually doing this? We're \Ninvestigating this stupid case?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.05,0:15:06.43,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.43,0:15:11.43,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,If he came drifting by in this state, \NMomotaro's body should be wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.43,0:15:13.96,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,You just called him Momotaro. \NYou admitted it is him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.96,0:15:19.08,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Also, can an old lady really drag a \Npeach with an adult inside all this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.93,0:15:20.88,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,There's something off here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.88,0:15:23.59,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, like an adult being inside a peach!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.93,0:15:27.04,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,The granny probably wasn't \Nalone when she found this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.04,0:15:28.09,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,What is Gramps's alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.09,0:15:29.84,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Cutting grass in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.84,0:15:30.99,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,That was an alibi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.99,0:15:33.09,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,It was something that scary?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.62,0:15:39.02,sign_22193_287_Old_Man__Possess,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Old Man\NPossession 1
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.91,0:15:39.02,sign_22200_288_Sickle,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Sickle
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.09,0:15:37.05,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Pops, get us a DNA comparison on \NGramps's sickle and Momotaro's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.05,0:15:39.02,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,What are you thinking? That's terrifying!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.33,0:15:42.52,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,The fatal wound matches the \Nway the peach was split.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:47.28,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, he was killed by the \Nold couple when they split the peach.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.28,0:15:49.61,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell kind of folktale is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.61,0:15:52.05,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't do it on purpose. \NIt was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.05,0:15:54.28,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,But that's why they fabricated alibis...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.28,0:15:55.91,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,You're mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.37,0:16:00.48,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you're the one who is \Nshackled by the story of Momotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.48,0:16:03.35,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you overlooked \Na vital piece of evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.35,0:16:04.34,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.34,0:16:07.71,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,You're too fixated on the man inside \Nthe peach, the granny's laundry,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.71,0:16:09.13,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,and Gramps's grass cutting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.82,0:16:14.57,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Hence, you assumed that this tragedy \Noccurred at the start of the Momotaro story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.57,0:16:17.43,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,But that's a mistake. Why, you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.73,0:16:23.48,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Ask yourself, why is Momotaro so big when \Nhe was only just born from the peach?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.48,0:16:25.26,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,You're taking issue with that now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.26,0:16:27.57,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,You ignore the "born from a peach" \Nthing and take issue with that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.50,0:16:30.57,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,And why are you shocked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.57,0:16:34.73,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Going from his filthy clothes \Nand the lack of kibi dango,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.73,0:16:37.66,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,we can tell that he'd already \Nfinished fighting the ogres.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.05,0:16:41.54,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,This incident happened \Nafter the end of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.54,0:16:44.45,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Then why was he inside a peach again?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.45,0:16:46.09,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.65,0:16:49.16,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,There's pretty much no sign of blood loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.16,0:16:53.47,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,This proves that he was already \Ndead when he got the wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.47,0:16:54.60,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,What that means is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.33,0:16:58.45,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody killed him and \Ndumped him in the river
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.45,0:17:01.68,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,in order to frame that old couple for murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.68,0:17:03.60,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Why is this getting so complicated?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.92,0:17:06.22,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,It was all camouflage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.22,0:17:09.09,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,But thanks to that, we can narrow \Ndown the list of suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.09,0:17:13.17,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,When you consider Momotaro's \Nsituation after fighting the ogres,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.17,0:17:14.87,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,the true culprit
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.50,0:17:19.54,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,can only be one of these three.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.94,0:17:24.16,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,It is said that Momotaro's party \Nbrought back treasure from Onigashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.16,0:17:27.78,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,But we're talking about animals \Nand a peach-born monster here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.78,0:17:31.27,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,It's not hard to picture them \Nfighting over the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.27,0:17:33.38,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,How much must you corrupt Momotaro \Nbefore you're satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.38,0:17:37.33,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Among them, the only one who can place \Nsuch a cunning trap is the mon—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.65,0:17:38.64,Main,Oki,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It wasn't the monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.46,0:17:45.15,Main,Oki,0000,0000,0000,,Shackled by the story of Momotaro, \Nyou overlooked something vital.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.66,0:17:49.48,Main,Oki,0000,0000,0000,,Monkeys can't use money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.48,0:17:51.72,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Why does Captain Obvious \Nhave such a smug look?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.72,0:17:53.65,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Their reasoning is getting \Nstupider by the minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.50,0:17:56.91,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,And why do you have a look of shock?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.91,0:18:01.52,Main,Oki,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the real culprit \Nis either the dog or the pheasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.52,0:18:03.46,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Dogs and pheasants can't use money, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.46,0:18:05.17,Main,Nob,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.48,0:18:07.67,Main,Nob,0000,0000,0000,,None of them is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.10,0:18:12.17,Main,Nob,0000,0000,0000,,You're so shackled by the Momotaro \Nstory that you've gone blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.17,0:18:15.18,Main,Oki,0000,0000,0000,,What? How can you say for sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.65,0:18:16.80,Main,Nob,0000,0000,0000,,Because that'd be a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:20.11,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,She ultimately wrote it off as a pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.11,0:18:22.43,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone would look shocked after that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:26.44,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they're all animals either way. \NCan't really question them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.83,0:18:28.97,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Pops, I'd like to see the autopsy report.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.97,0:18:31.78,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,There must be another fatal wound somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.78,0:18:33.44,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to say this, Toshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.89,0:18:36.76,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,but this is the only external \Nwound that stands out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.76,0:18:40.33,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,However, x-rays did find something \Nstrange in his trachea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.58,0:18:44.08,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Something shaped like a dango.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.08,0:18:47.13,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, he totally died choking on kibi dango!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.13,0:18:49.91,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,This is why I can't stand plebs. \NThat's not kibi dango.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.91,0:18:52.01,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,It's what the monkey pooped out \Nafter eating the kibi dango.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.01,0:18:55.17,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,You know how monkeys throw their own poop? \NI knew it, the monkey was the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.17,0:18:57.61,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,I was right. An elite was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.61,0:18:58.55,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Praise the elite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.55,0:18:59.85,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,You're not thinking like an elite now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.85,0:19:04.38,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,You stupid? The gramps and gran would \Nobviously be the ones feeding him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.38,0:19:08.02,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Tempted by the treasure, they choked \Nhim to death using kibi dango.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.02,0:19:10.67,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,The old farts really were \Nthe culprits. I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.67,0:19:11.77,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Praise mayonnaise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.77,0:19:13.86,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you paint them in a \Ntotally different light before?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.86,0:19:14.76,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,The monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.76,0:19:15.83,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Gramps and gran.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.83,0:19:16.44,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,The monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.44,0:19:17.68,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Gramps and gran.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.68,0:19:18.93,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,The monkey's gramps and gran.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.93,0:19:20.45,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Gramps and gran's monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.45,0:19:21.99,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,We agreed it was the monkey just now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.99,0:19:26.25,Main,Oki,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, fine. Let's take the middle option \Nand say it was the eunuch monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.25,0:19:28.46,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Middle option of what? \NWhere'd the gramps and gran go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.46,0:19:31.21,Main,Nob,0000,0000,0000,,It can be Monkey and Aska's \Ngramps and gran, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.21,0:19:32.50,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what happened to Chage?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.84,0:19:35.34,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, let's settle \Nthis once and for all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.71,0:19:38.06,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Director-General, it doesn't \Nmatter if they're animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.06,0:19:40.92,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Let us question Momotaro's party.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.92,0:19:42.89,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, if you want them...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.12,0:19:45.16,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,They're in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.16,0:19:47.48,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,All the suspects have been eaten!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.48,0:19:52.14,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, are you saying Momotaro \Nwas the perpetrator?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.58,0:19:55.16,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.52,0:20:00.44,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,They were stranded on the \Nway back from Onigashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.81,0:20:04.79,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,The sad fate of his party is proof enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.22,0:20:10.88,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of treasure, they fought to eat \Neach other's kibi dango and bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.36,0:20:14.88,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,And almost like divine punishment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.29,0:20:20.51,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,the last bite, his friend's kibi \Ndango, got caught in his throat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.48,0:20:25.51,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,The one who killed him was \Nnone other than himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.06,0:20:28.46,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,No way... That can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.90,0:20:33.41,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,How can such a laughable cause of \Ndeath turn into something so sad?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.22,0:20:35.52,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Toshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.52,0:20:38.06,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,This is what the field is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.50,0:20:43.82,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,It shoves harsh realities and even \Nharsher truths right into our faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.55,0:20:47.25,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,But we must not avert our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.62,0:20:53.50,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,As cops, we have the duty to find the \Ntruth even if it's shrouded in darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.44,0:20:55.84,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,T-Toshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.01,0:20:59.29,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.69,0:21:03.59,sign_30035_398_No_sneaking_bite,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,No sneaking bites.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.42,0:21:01.53,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.53,0:21:03.59,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,It likely had kibi dango inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.85,0:21:08.65,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,He probably didn't eat a single dango.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.65,0:21:12.89,sign_30250_401_No_sneaking_bite,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,No sneaking bites.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.10,0:21:12.89,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,He must've given them all to his friends \Nand chewed on his sandals or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.72,0:21:16.55,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,But they went down one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.55,0:21:18.30,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,Considering how he could eat crap like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.30,0:21:20.34,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,he must've ended up being the last one alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.93,0:21:24.35,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of the story is as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.35,0:21:27.37,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,He chose that path in order to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.69,0:21:32.10,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,You can't eat a bag like this \Nunless you have extreme resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.10,0:21:33.96,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,He must've really wanted to live...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.96,0:21:35.63,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,His friends' share of life, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.64,0:21:37.88,Main,Kon,0000,0000,0000,,Toshi...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.88,0:21:42.01,Main,Isa,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that sappy crap \Nwas the kind of reality you saw?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.01,0:21:43.31,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.31,0:21:46.39,Main,Hij,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth I believe in, \Nthe truth I found at this crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.39,0:21:47.97,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Bzzt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.02,0:21:54.98,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad. Close, but no cigar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.30,0:21:58.37,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,You got the "Momotaro was killed" part right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.37,0:22:01.20,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,But this isn't Momotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.14,0:22:07.84,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,It's the boss of Onigashima, who ate \Nthe entire Momotaro party alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.84,0:22:12.04,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Disguised as Momotaro, he came to \Nthe mainland to eat more humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.04,0:22:14.96,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,But he died without achieving his goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.68,0:22:16.79,sign_31785_421_Cause_of_Death,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Cause of Death
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.96,0:22:16.79,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,Basically,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.10,0:22:22.74,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,the real culprit is a brain tumor. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.74,0:22:24.12,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.80,0:22:25.80,Ep Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(900,1)}The End
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.12,0:22:25.80,Main,Mat,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.85,0:24:00.81,Ep Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(440,1)}3000 Leagues in Search of a Scabbard
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.06,0:24:00.10,Main,Gin,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: "3000 Leagues \Nin Search of a Scabbard."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.81,0:24:05.82,Side Bar Top,TextR,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, it's been a while since \Nwe've seen Tetsuko,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.81,0:24:05.82,Side Bar Bottom,TextL,0000,0000,0000,,but she has a fair amount of screen \Ntime, like in the live-action movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.82,0:24:12.24,Side Bar Top,TextR,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps because he treated swords\N like crap at a smithy,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.82,0:24:12.24,Side Bar Bottom,TextL,0000,0000,0000,,Gintoki's butthole gets attacked by one!
